1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:12,033
<i> Hey! Who are you?</i>

2
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:13,167
<i> I'll call the cops!</i>

3
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:16,667
<i>What are you doing to Mookie?
Who are they?</i>

4
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,333
<i> Emma?</i>

5
00:00:17,467 --> 00:00:18,900
<i> What the hell, Emma?</i>

6
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:20,367
<i>You're forgetting
about the plan.</i>

7
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,500
<i> Let's just dance.</i>

8
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:22,567
<i> Why are you fighting with me?</i>

9
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:23,433
<i> What are you doing?</i>

10
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:26,033
<i>Do you know what my problem is?</i>

11
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:27,267
<i> My mother!</i>

12
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,900
<i>I still can't accept
that she left us.</i>

13
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:32,300
<i> I don't know how to dance.</i>

14
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:35,200
<i> I only dance with my partner.</i>

15
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:36,500
<i> With Emma.</i>

16
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:37,967
<i>Let's show them
what we're made of.</i>

17
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:40,300
<i> I was away for a while,</i>

18
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:43,033
<i>and someone already wanted
to steal my fiancé.</i>

19
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> Hey! Let me go!</i>

20
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:46,433
<i> Are you going to stop her?</i>

21
00:00:46,567 --> 00:00:47,900
<i>Are you going to attack
the woman?</i>

22
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:48,933
<i> Yes.</i>

23
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:51,767
<i>Because I won't let anyone steal
my fiancé.</i>

24
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:53,600
<i> Watch me, Jade.</i>

25
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:55,700
<i> No!</i>

26
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:33,567
No!

27
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:36,367
Jade.

28
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,633
- Stay away from my fiancé!
- Jade, stop!

29
00:01:38,767 --> 00:01:42,833
Of all the men out here,
why do you flirt with my fiancé?

30
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,733
- Jade, stop!
- Show me your face!

31
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:56,933
I said show me your face!
Face me!

32
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,067
I'm not done with you yet!

33
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,067
Let me go!

34
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,000
Stop!

35
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:20,733
I'm not done with you yet!
Come here!

36
00:02:22,967 --> 00:02:24,400
Wait, wait.

37
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:32,233
She's so unfair, Zayn.

38
00:02:35,433 --> 00:02:39,733
She promised me that she
wouldn't leave me.

39
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:42,300
She would take care of me.

40
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:50,867
But she didn't fulfill all her
promises.

41
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,333
That's enough.

42
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:59,200
Sorry, I didn't know you felt
that way.

43
00:03:00,967 --> 00:03:02,267
But the way I see it,

44
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:05,000
you're mad because of the pain.

45
00:03:08,433 --> 00:03:10,167
I'm mad because of the pain?

46
00:03:12,133 --> 00:03:13,233
No, Zayn.

47
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:16,333
I hate her.

48
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,900
I hate her so much.

49
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,900
I hate her more than
I hate Mommy Olive.

50
00:03:25,033 --> 00:03:26,033
Do you know why?

51
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:32,967
Because Mommy Olive made me get
used to the pain.

52
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,933
But my mom...

53
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:39,067
Zayn,

54
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:45,333
I felt nothing
but love from her.

55
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:48,167
She made me feel loved.

56
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:50,900
That's what I got used
to with her.

57
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:53,100
And I thought it would be
forever.

58
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,067
But what did she do?

59
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:57,767
She didn't care about me, Zayn.

60
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:59,633
She only made my hopes up.

61
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:06,067
Just when I thought we would
forever be happy

62
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,633
and stay together as family...

63
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,167
she left us.

64
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:18,833
So don't expect the old Mookie
to return.

65
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:22,100
Because she will never come
back.

66
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:25,333
My mom made me like this.

67
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:29,000
You're saying that because
you're still hurting, Mooks.

68
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:31,133
No, Zayn.

69
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,267
Didn't you say you like me?

70
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,133
Go!

71
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:38,167
Like someone else.

72
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,833
I don't care even if I like you

73
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:43,267
because the old Mookie will
never return.

74
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:45,600
Wait.

75
00:04:46,933 --> 00:04:47,967
You like me too?

76
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:57,400
What do you mean like?
I didn't say anything like that.

77
00:04:58,867 --> 00:05:00,033
You just said it, Mooks.

78
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:18,967
Where do you think you're going?

79
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:20,367
Come here!

80
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:24,600
Why did you have to flirt with
my fiancé

81
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:25,767
of all the men out there?

82
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:28,333
You seduced the wrong man.

83
00:05:28,467 --> 00:05:29,767
Because he's mine!

84
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:33,267
He belongs to a lioness
who will never back down!

85
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,833
Show me your face!

86
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:35,467
Why?

87
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,267
Damn it!

88
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:44,967
Jade!

89
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,267
That's enough, Jade!

90
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,733
No!

91
00:05:50,867 --> 00:05:51,800
Jade!

92
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,900
Hello, I'm going downstairs.

93
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,667
Where are you going?

94
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,300
You can't escape me!

95
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:11,433
I will only let you flirt with
Danilo once you're crippled.

96
00:06:11,567 --> 00:06:13,633
Why don't you show me your face?

97
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:19,167
Emma?

98
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:25,433
No.

99
00:06:26,133 --> 00:06:27,367
I knew it! It's you!

100
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:38,633
Move.

101
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:43,267
Maybe you heard it wrong.

102
00:06:49,067 --> 00:06:50,367
You know...

103
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:56,033
Since you can now walk
and seem okay, you can go home.

104
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,033
Admit it first.

105
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:00,600
What do I have to admit?

106
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:04,633
Mooks, nothing is wrong in
admitting your feelings.

107
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:07,700
But, fine.

108
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:10,167
I won't force you if you
don't want to.

109
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:15,733
Fine.

110
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,800
I like you.

111
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:19,700
Happy?

112
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:23,700
But it doesn't matter anymore,
Zayn.

113
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,233
Of course it does, Mooks.

114
00:07:26,233 --> 00:07:27,900
That's why I wanted
to talk to you.

115
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:30,300
Because I realized

116
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:35,167
I couldn't stand by what I told
you last time.

117
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:39,167
I can't let go of our
friendship.

118
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:41,267
I know you'll eventually
dislike me, Zayn.

119
00:07:43,733 --> 00:07:46,967
Because the Mookie you know
will never return.

120
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,000
I won't force you to change back
to the old Mookie.

121
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,300
Even if you become bad.

122
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:56,033
Even if you become harsh to me.

123
00:07:59,867 --> 00:08:01,600
That won't change
the fact that...

124
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,000
I like you.

125
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:07,667
I like you very much.

126
00:08:12,433 --> 00:08:15,300
Mooks, I know you'll go back
to your old self.

127
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:16,600
Because that's you.

128
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:25,733
You're kind, happy despite
the problems,

129
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:30,000
and very patient even if you're
bullied.

130
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:33,733
You're only behaving like that
because you're still hurting.

131
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:39,667
But that pain will eventually
disappear.

132
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:42,933
And I'll stay with you
while you heal.

133
00:08:44,167 --> 00:08:46,333
I'll be here whether you like it
or not.

134
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,533
What now?

135
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,433
That's enough.
I've already calmed down.

136
00:08:59,267 --> 00:09:00,067
One more round.

137
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,500
Come here.

138
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:02,533
Shut up.

139
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:03,600
You can cry now.

140
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:04,333
Go on.

141
00:09:04,467 --> 00:09:06,067
Are you calling for backup?

142
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,600
Call everyone!

143
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:09,500
You're so loud.

144
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:14,633
Jade, answer the call.

145
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,167
Hello?

146
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:17,900
Leticia.

147
00:09:18,033 --> 00:09:18,933
Where are you guys?

148
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:20,833
I'm here in the lobby.

149
00:09:20,967 --> 00:09:22,233
Is Jade not with you?

150
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:24,700
No. But I saw her going
to the parking area.

151
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,633
Okay, I'll go there.

152
00:09:30,933 --> 00:09:32,667
Oh, he's going home.

153
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,633
Come here!

154
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:35,100
One more!

155
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:36,167
One more!

156
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:41,100
Boss, I know where Emma is.

157
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:12,667
Where are you?

158
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,133
Emma?

159
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:20,967
Emma!

160
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,767
You can't escape me.
Don't you remember?

161
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,200
I'm Satan's daughter.

162
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:32,033
So I can throw you in hell the
moment you steal Danilo from me.

163
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,467
You can never escape me, Emma.

164
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:39,433
I got you.

165
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:46,200
Gotcha!

166
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:49,167
Boss, wait!

167
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,467
Can you calm down?

168
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,067
I can't!

169
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,000
What if Jade catches Emma?

170
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:55,600
All our plans will get ruined.

171
00:10:55,733 --> 00:10:57,200
It won't get ruined.

172
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,467
How can you be so sure?

173
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:04,567
Our backup is waiting
at the parking area.

174
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:09,433
Ma'am, that hurts.

175
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,200
Stop pretending.

176
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:12,700
I know you're Emma.

177
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:14,400
I'm not Emma.

178
00:11:14,533 --> 00:11:16,200
My name's Marie.

179
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:18,800
Remember our plan B?

180
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:22,400
Marie will come to the rescue
when things get tough.

181
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,533
Are you sure she's there?

182
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:33,800
I talked to her on the phone
earlier.

183
00:11:33,933 --> 00:11:35,500
She said Emma called her.

184
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:37,967
She knows what to do.

185
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:43,067
Good.

186
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:44,933
Good job.

187
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:53,133
You've been chasing me
since earlier.

188
00:11:53,267 --> 00:11:54,400
Come here.

189
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:57,600
Come here, you witch.
Stop fooling me.

190
00:11:57,733 --> 00:11:58,800
I know you're Emma.

191
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:07,433
Get lost!

192
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,767
I'm sure I saw Emma.

193
00:12:33,267 --> 00:12:34,633
I've already escaped Jade.

194
00:12:36,233 --> 00:12:37,900
I'm outside the hotel.

195
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,167
Emma!

196
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:44,233
Emma!

197
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:50,867
Emma, I know it's you.

198
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:55,767
I told you I'm not Emma.

199
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,433
Don't you have any plans
to be with Mookie again?

200
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,367
I'm not Emma.

201
00:13:12,633 --> 00:13:14,033
I know it's you, Emma.

202
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:17,700
The smell of your cologne...

203
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,533
Our dance...

204
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:24,667
You can't deny those, Emma.

205
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:28,633
Don't look for your wife.

206
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:30,867
I'm not her.

207
00:13:32,367 --> 00:13:35,967
Turn around if you're telling
the truth.

208
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:39,033
Show me your face.

209
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,133
Emma...

210
00:13:50,167 --> 00:13:50,933
She misses...

211
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:55,233
Mookie misses you a lot.

212
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:06,200
Even if she doesn't tell me,
I know she's hurting.

213
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,200
I'm not Emma.

214
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,367
Emma, please.

215
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:20,900
Come back.

216
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:27,367
If not for me... Do it for
Mookie.

217
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:38,433
Are you sure you're okay?

218
00:14:38,567 --> 00:14:41,000
Why don't you ask your dad
to pick you up?

219
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:43,533
I suddenly felt fine when
I heard that my crush liked me.

220
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,800
Nothing hurts anymore.

221
00:14:47,933 --> 00:14:50,467
I can still drive to Baguio.

222
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:51,333
Do you want to come?

223
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:58,033
But I'm serious, Mooks.

224
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,833
I'm here for you.

225
00:15:01,933 --> 00:15:05,267
I won't leave you no matter
what you go through.

226
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:10,433
I know that, Zayn.

227
00:15:12,767 --> 00:15:17,767
You've never left me since
the first time we met.

228
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:24,300
You've always been good to me,
Zayn.

229
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:26,667
But me...

230
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:30,433
I mistreated you.

231
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:37,333
That's enough.

232
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:39,500
Don't cry.

233
00:15:40,867 --> 00:15:42,033
Smile now.

234
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:42,967
Okay?

235
00:15:44,933 --> 00:15:47,000
Let's forget about that.

236
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:49,767
What matters is we're okay.

237
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:54,400
I'll do everything
for us to be okay.

238
00:15:58,633 --> 00:15:59,467
So?

239
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:39,567
I told you I'm not Emma.

240
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:50,467
Emma, I'm begging you.

241
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:54,167
Come back for your daughter.

242
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:57,833
Let's go!

243
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,400
Come back for your daughter.

244
00:17:06,533 --> 00:17:07,300
Emma!

245
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:09,433
Emma!

246
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,833
Even just for your daughter.

247
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:45,333
Jade!

248
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,800
Some things are not adding up.

249
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:51,400
Emma.

250
00:17:58,167 --> 00:17:58,733
<i> Emma?</i>

251
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,133
<i>Come here, you witch.
Stop fooling me.</i>

252
00:18:03,267 --> 00:18:04,333
<i> I know you're Emma!</i>

253
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:09,367
She's Emma.

254
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,767
Emma's dead.

255
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,500
Didn't we see her in the photo?

256
00:18:13,633 --> 00:18:14,867
She was in a grave.

257
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:20,600
Jade, wait.

258
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,667
Are you taking your medicine?

259
00:18:26,033 --> 00:18:26,567
No.

260
00:18:27,667 --> 00:18:29,733
I no longer need
to take any medicine.

261
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:31,667
I've been okay for a long time.

262
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:32,567
What?

263
00:18:34,167 --> 00:18:37,367
Jade, you've been diagnosed with
hallucinatory trace disorder.

264
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:40,467
Pryvaxil is your lifetime
maintenance.

265
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:44,800
You shouldn't take it only
when you feel like it.

266
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:45,867
What are you doing?

267
00:18:51,467 --> 00:18:52,867
Where have you been?

268
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:55,633
Did you follow that woman?

269
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,067
Why?

270
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,867
Is it because you want to finish
your dance? Is that it?

271
00:19:00,967 --> 00:19:04,500
You want to flirt with her,
don't you? Answer me!

272
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:05,533
Come on, Jade. Let's go home.

273
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:06,367
No!

274
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:09,700
We'll finish it here!

275
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,133
So answer me!

276
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:15,900
Do you want to flirt with
that woman?

277
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:17,167
Answer me!

278
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:18,933
Yes!

279
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,733
Because I thought she was Emma!

280
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,333
Didn't you follow her

281
00:19:24,467 --> 00:19:25,667
because you also thought she was
Emma?

282
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,700
No!

283
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:29,500
The question is
is she really Emma?

284
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:31,367
Is she?

285
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,733
I followed her
because I was jealous!

286
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,900
I wanted to hurt her!

287
00:19:40,033 --> 00:19:41,733
And that's what I did!

288
00:19:41,867 --> 00:19:43,867
I put her where she belongs!

289
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:47,167
And she's not Emma.

290
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:50,467
You're wrong to think she's
Emma!

291
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:54,300
She's just some cheap whore
who's hungry for men!

292
00:19:56,833 --> 00:20:01,167
How can you be so sure
that your wife has a lover?

293
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:06,433
Maybe that's what you want
to believe to justify your sins.

294
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:09,600
Jade, I want to know.

295
00:20:09,733 --> 00:20:11,567
Did Emma really leave
with another man?

296
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,967
Why are you asking me that?

297
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:17,000
Yes!

298
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:21,567
If that's true,
what's the man's name?

299
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:22,900
How old is he?

300
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:24,000
Where does he live?

301
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,733
And why did Emma go
with that man?

302
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:29,833
I didn't ask the private
investigator

303
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:31,533
because it doesn't matter!

304
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:35,133
What will you do if when you
find it out?

305
00:20:36,267 --> 00:20:37,467
Do you think she'll come back?

306
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:40,967
Danilo, she's gone forever!

307
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:43,433
She left you for another man!

308
00:20:43,567 --> 00:20:46,033
She loves someone else,
and it's not you!

309
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:49,167
Emma is gone!

310
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:51,367
She's gone forever!

311
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:08,900
Boss, this came earlier.

312
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:10,700
Leave it there.

313
00:21:10,833 --> 00:21:12,033
Thank you, Marco.

314
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,167
Is this what we'll use?

315
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:20,333
Yes.

316
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:32,200
Emma, when you were dancing...

317
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:37,000
would you really kiss Danilo
if Jade hadn't stopped you?

318
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,333
Yes.

319
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:43,667
So Jade would be
even more jealous.

320
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:46,067
Kissing him wasn't part
of the plan!

321
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,133
There's nothing wrong with that.

322
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:49,000
He's my husband.

323
00:21:49,133 --> 00:21:50,000
That was before, Emma!

324
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:52,700
That was before!

325
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,567
Jade.

326
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:07,167
- Love...
- What happened?

327
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:09,300
Love, please. Please, stop.

328
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:11,533
Love, I don't want us fighting.

329
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:14,367
So please, let's stop.

330
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:18,233
I don't want us to be like this
because of Emma.

331
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:23,267
That woman is like a ghost
that doesn't leave us!

332
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:27,533
I don't want this for us too.

333
00:22:27,667 --> 00:22:30,167
I don't want us to fight.

334
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:34,367
Please, please.
I feel so insecure.

335
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,400
That's the truth.

336
00:22:35,533 --> 00:22:38,933
I feel insecure about Emma.

337
00:22:39,067 --> 00:22:43,000
Because we always
talk about her.

338
00:22:43,133 --> 00:22:43,933
She's always our topic.

339
00:22:44,067 --> 00:22:45,600
So, please. Please, Danilo.

340
00:22:45,733 --> 00:22:48,133
Promise me.

341
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:52,800
Promise me that we'll never
talk about Emma anymore.

342
00:22:52,933 --> 00:22:54,067
Please.

343
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,533
Please.

344
00:22:55,667 --> 00:22:57,100
Please.

345
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:26,100
Let me remind you that
that man fooled you.

346
00:23:28,967 --> 00:23:32,133
Emma, I need to know.

347
00:23:32,267 --> 00:23:34,033
Tell me the truth.

348
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,967
Do you still love Danilo?

349
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:50,833
Danilo belongs to me,
and Emma belongs to you.

350
00:23:50,967 --> 00:23:53,767
We need to stop them from
getting back together.

351
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:54,933
<i> The revelations</i>

352
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:58,500
<i>- aren't over yet.
- Mom?</i>

353
00:23:58,633 --> 00:23:59,567
Stop the wedding!

354
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:00,633
What are you doing here?

355
00:24:00,767 --> 00:24:01,867
You're messing
everything up again!

356
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,533
No matter how you pretend,
your true colors still show!

357
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:09,233
Did you come back because
you realized it's me you love?

358
00:24:09,367 --> 00:24:12,033
No. You're a murderer.

359
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:13,267
I'm your mother!

360
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,900
You belong to me only!
